Project: the non-toy m7 fixture WITH an opt-in mutation gate (D35).

Same two-module core+web project as the base six-pack fixture, plus a genuine
mutation-testing gate. The project owns the standard (threshold 80); the harness
owns execution + verdict. `core/rules.sh` is a small pure-logic module under
mutation; `core/rules-test.sh` is its unit test whose strength the mutants probe.
`tools/mutation-run.sh` is the project's declared mutation command — a genuine
miniature that mutates rules.sh, runs rules-test.sh against each mutant, and emits
a PITest-shaped mutations.xml so the runner reads a REAL score (never hard-coded).

owns:
  core/**
  web/**
  features/**
  acceptance/steps.sh
test: bash run-unit.sh
quality:
  architecture: bash tools/arch-check.sh
  dup: bash tools/dup-check.sh
accept: bash acceptance/run-acceptance.sh
mutation:
  tool: pitest
  threshold: 80
  command: bash tools/mutation-run.sh
